properties.provenance: Webster, William Downing (1868-1913) In 1899 he travelled throughout Britain purchasing material from British soldiers returning from the Benin Expedition, amassing a large quantity of material that was carefully recorded in his catalogues. He published a series of catalogues detailing his collection during the next two decades, and staged a number of exhibitions of ethnographic material at Earl's Court.

Webster sold the entirety of his collection in a five-day auction in 1904 after his divorce. Sold to Hans Meyer (collector) a German geology professor from Hildburghausen, later the director of the Institute for Colonial Geography in Leipzig.
After death to Grassi Museum of Ethnopology in Leipzig
